    "body": "### Description\n\nWhen editing Astro files, using Blink-cmp as my completion plugin, I am only able to get component suggestions in the HTML section of the file if I start typing the component name in insert mode, then hit escape to go to normal mode, and then re-enter insert mode and then either continue typing or invoking the auto-complete. Without doing this, I only get snippets as suggestions.\n\nThis bug doesn't happen in normal typescript projects, or within the frontmatter section. With these, the auto-suggestions work as expected.\n\n`:LspInfo` shows that astro is active and attached. ",
